value.name: Yr Eifl - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Yr Eifl, sometimes called the Rivals in English, is a group of hills on the north coast of the Llŷn Peninsula in Gwynedd, Wales. On a clear day, the views from the highest summit reach as far as the Isle of Man , the Wicklow Mountains in Ireland and the Lake District , as well as the entire sweep of Cardigan Bay .

value.name: International Fight League - Wikipedia
value.snippet: The IFL consisted of nine camps, all owned by the league, and each coached by a veteran MMA fighter. Originally the IFL had teams that were associated with cities but that proved to be a lark as many of the teams did not train in their respective cities nor did all the fighters live in those cities as well.
